result.execSummary:
The defendant Kimberly Ruth Pabst was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Resisting or Obstructing an Officer, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.41(1).
  • OWI (3rd), an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

miscConds.notes: AS TO BOTH COUNTS: Provide DNA sample and pay DNA surcharges, the fine ordered in Count 2, plus all other costs and disbursements. Failure to pay would result in a civil judgment entered against defendant.

AS TO BOTH COUNTS:
- Undergo a Mental Health Evaluation; follow through with any treatment recommended.
- No controlled substances other than those legally prescribed for defendant by a duly licensed physician for her mental or physical needs; take as prescribed for only as long as deemed medically reasonable and necessary.
- No alcohol.
- Urine screens to ensure compliance.
- Parenting classes.
- Cognitive thinking intervention counseling.
- Seek/maintain employment.
- Job and vocational training.
- No Contact with the victim, Kay W.
